---
description: Authentication — Admin/Teacher username+password via Supabase Auth, phone as recovery/2FA only
globs: ["apps/api/**/auth/**", "apps/api/**", "packages/db/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Reference: `ARCHITECTURE.md` Part 1, "Authentication."

- **Scope is Admin + Teacher only.** Never add a password/auth column to
  any guardian-related table or endpoint. Guardians stay WhatsApp-only,
  self-created via the WhatsApp handshake — no exceptions without an
  explicit product decision, since this is currently an open tension (see
  `CLAUDE.md` §7), not a settled design.

- **Phone/WhatsApp OTP is recovery + 2FA only.** Never build or accept a
  code path where phone/OTP alone is sufficient to log in an Admin or
  Teacher — that would silently undo the confirmed "password is primary"
  decision. OTP verification for recovery ends in the backend calling the
  Supabase Admin API to set a new password directly
  (`admin.updateUserById`), never Supabase's own email-based reset flow.

- **No self-registration.** There is no public sign-up endpoint for Admin
  or Teacher. An `identities` row always starts as
  `account_status = 'invited'`, created by an admin. Don't add a "create
  my own account" flow.

- **The synthetic email for mobile-only accounts is an internal
  implementation detail — it must never leak.** Never display it in a UI,
  never log it in a way that implies it's a real contact address, never
  send an actual email to it (it isn't real), and never write it to
  `identities.email` (that column is real-emails-only, nullable). It exists
  solely as a value passed to Supabase Auth calls, computed by
  `AuthService.resolveIdentifierToEmail()`.

- **`school_memberships.member_type = 'admin'` gates admin-only endpoints
  only — it is not a substitute for the two-grain `teacher_sections` scope
  checks.** An admin still has no implicit read/write access to child data;
  every `SectionSubjectWriteGuard`/`SectionReadGuard` check still applies to
  admin accounts exactly as it does to teacher accounts. If you're tempted
  to write `if (user.role === 'admin') { skip the scope check }`, don't —
  that violates the gravity rule.

- **`account_status = 'disabled'` must fail closed independent of the
  underlying Supabase Auth session.** Don't assume disabling an identity
  also invalidates their Supabase Auth token automatically — the RLS
  function `current_identity_id()` in
  `20250718120000_identity_tenant_auth.sql` already checks
  `account_status = 'active'` explicitly; don't remove that check or
  assume it's redundant.

- **`SupabaseAuthGuard` runs before any RBAC guard, on every protected
  route**, resolving the bearer token to an `identities` row (then
  membership + teacher/admin profile) and attaching that to the request. RLS
  is defense-in-depth underneath this — it is not a substitute for the
  NestJS guard actually running first.
